[2026-03-18T17:11:26.651Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Extract event lifecycle as explicit state machine\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: maintenance\n- **Effort**: Unknown (4/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (7/3)\n- **Scan Type**: insight_synth\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 9:34:21 AM\n\n## Description\nEvent status transitions (pending -> processing -> delivered/skipped/failed/partial) are scattered across eventProcessor.ts and db.ts as raw string comparisons. Define the valid states and transitions as a first-class TypeScript discriminated union or state machine (e.g., a transition map object). Validate transitions at the db layer so invalid state changes throw rather than silently corrupt. Add a new partial-retry state to enable re-processing of events where some but not all subscription matches failed.\n\n## Reasoning\nThe implicit state machine makes it easy to introduce invalid transitions (e.g., processing -> pending only via the reaper). Formalizing it makes the event lifecycle self-documenting, prevents bugs from impossible transitions, and creates a foundation for observability dashboards that visualize event flow through states. The partial status already hints at needing richer lifecycle semantics.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\nUse Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3557cb6e-ae5f-4c9b-abbc-8aa3f1b3f2e1","uuid":"57ac0c21-f9f4-41b6-83df-8216e097dbfc","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:11:26.567Z","isSynthetic":true}
